<p style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:
0in'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;color:black'>No emergency
assistance required.</span></p>

<p style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:
0in'><b><span style='font-size:18.0pt;color:black'>Classification</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
color:black'>·<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;color:black'>Androgenetic
alopecia (male type) is the most common form, the development of which is based
on a genetic predisposition.&nbsp;More common in men.&nbsp;Thinning and hair
loss occurs, leading to baldness of the parietal and frontal regions (in women
- to thinning hair in the central part of the head with spreading to its
lateral surfaces).&nbsp;</span><span style='font-size:13.5pt;color:black'>This
form progresses with age.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;color:black'>Diffuse
alopecia - uniform hair loss across the entire scalp as a result of disturbed
hair cycles.&nbsp;The second most common form, women suffer more often than
men.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;color:black'>Alopecia areata
(alopecia areata) - hair loss as a result of autoimmune damage to hair
follicles and sometimes nail plates.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;color:black'>Cicatricial
alopecia - hair loss due to the irreversible destruction of the hair follicle
during trauma.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
